  <section>
    <h2>TIG Facing of AlCoCrFeNiCu Alloy on Stainless Steel</h2>

    <h3>Objective</h3>
    <p>
      To enhance mechanical properties in high-strength applications using hard facing
      of high entropy alloy (HEA) on stainless steel, leading to increased hardness
      and wear resistance.
    </p>

    <h3>Methodology</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Used TIG welding process with AlCoCrFeNiCu alloy on AISI 316 stainless steel.</li>
      <li>Current: 12 A (AC), Speed: 0.8 mm/sec, Electrode gap: 2.5 mm with Argon shielding.</li>
      <li>Characterization carried out using SEM, EDS, Vickers hardness test, and Pin-on-disc wear test.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Results and Discussion</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Hardness improved from 152 HV to 280 HV, representing a 1.84× increase.</li>
      <li>
        Wear tests were conducted using a pin-on-disc setup at 500 rpm under loads of
        30 N, 50 N, and 70 N. The wear rate values obtained were
        5.52 × 10<sup>-7</sup> g/Nm,
        3.51 × 10<sup>-7</sup> g/Nm, and
        3.81 × 10<sup>-7</sup> g/Nm respectively.
      </li>
      <li>SEM analysis revealed grain refinement and improved wear-resistant microstructural features.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Vickers Hardness Calculation (Discussion)</h3>
    <p>
      The Vickers hardness value was calculated using the diagonal lengths of the square
      indentation measured with an optical microscope.
    </p>

    <p><strong>Measured Diagonals:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>d<sub>1</sub> = 0.346 mm</li>
      <li>d<sub>2</sub> = 0.352 mm</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Average Diagonal Length:</strong></p>
    <p>
      d = (d<sub>1</sub> + d<sub>2</sub>) / 2 = (0.346 + 0.352) / 2 = <strong>0.349 mm</strong>
    </p>

    <p><strong>Vickers Hardness Formula:</strong></p>
    <p>
      HV = 1.854 × F / d²
    </p>

    <p>
      Substituting the measured average diagonal value:
    </p>

    <p>
      HV = 1.854 × 10 / (0.349)² ≈ <strong>152 HV</strong>
    </p>

    <p>
      This value represents the baseline hardness of the untreated stainless steel
      substrate and serves as a reference for evaluating the hardness enhancement
      achieved after TIG hard facing with the AlCoCrFeNiCu high entropy alloy.
    </p>
