    <h3>Microstructure & Analysis</h3>
    <p>
      SEM and EDS analyses confirmed uniform dispersion of alloying elements,
      refined microstructure, and well-defined wear tracks, contributing to
      improved wear resistance.
    </p>

    <div style="text-align:center; margin:2rem 0;">
  <img src="sem.gif" style="max-width:300px; border:5px solid black;">
</div>
   
    <div class="caption">
      <div style="text-align:center; margin:2rem 0;">
      Figure: SEM microstructure of AlCoCrFeNiCu HEA coated SS 316 substrate after Pin on Disc Test.
</div>

    <h3>Applications</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Tool materials</li>
      <li>Aerospace and defense components (tanks, howitzers)</li>
      <li>Functional and protective coatings</li>
      <li>Transport and heavy engineering industries</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Advantages</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Significant improvement in hardness and wear resistance</li>
      <li>Enhanced corrosion resistance</li>
      <li>Extended service life of components</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Conclusion</h3>
    <p>
      TIG hard facing with AlCoCrFeNiCu high entropy alloy provides a reliable and
      high-performance alternative to conventional coatings on stainless steel,
      making it suitable for demanding industrial applications.
    </p>

